  "chapter": {
    "number": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment to Continue"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then the LORD said to me: “Even if Moses and Samuel should stand before Me, My heart would not go out to this people. Send them from My presence, and let them go."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "If they ask you, ‘Where shall we go?’ you are to tell them that this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Those destined for death, to death;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those destined for the sword, to the sword;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2885
          },
          {
            "text": "those destined for famine, to famine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those destined for captivity, to captivity.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "I will appoint over them four kinds of destroyers, declares the LORD: the sword to kill, the dogs to drag away, and the birds of the air and beasts of the earth to devour and destroy."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "I will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth because of what Manasseh son of Hezekiah king of Judah did in Jerusalem."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who will have pity on you, O Jerusalem?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will mourn for you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will turn aside",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to ask about your welfare?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have forsaken Me, declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You have turned your back.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So I will stretch out My hand against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will destroy you;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I am weary of showing compassion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will scatter them with a winnowing fork",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at the gates of the land.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bereave and destroy My people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who have not turned from their ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make their widows more numerous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than the sand of the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bring a destroyer at noon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against the mothers of young men.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will suddenly bring upon them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "anguish and dismay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The mother of seven will grow faint;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "she will breathe her last breath.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Her sun will set while it is still day;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "she will be disgraced and humiliated.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And the rest I will put to the sword",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the presence of their enemies,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Jeremiah’s Woe"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to me, my mother,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you have borne me,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a man of strife and conflict",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in all the land.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have neither lent nor borrowed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet everyone curses me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "The LORD said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Surely I will deliver you for a good purpose;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "surely I will intercede with your enemy",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in your time of trouble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in your time of distress.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can anyone smash iron—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "iron from the north—or bronze?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your wealth and your treasures",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will give up as plunder,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "without charge for all your sins",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "within all your borders.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I will enslave you to your enemies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in a land",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2886
          },
          {
            "text": "you do not know,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for My anger will kindle a fire",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that will burn against you.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You understand, O LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "remember me and attend to me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Avenge me against my persecutors.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "In Your patience, do not take me away.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Know that I endure reproach for Your honor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your words were found, and I ate them.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Your words became my joy",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and my heart’s delight.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For I bear Your name,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O LORD God of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I never sat with the band of revelers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor did I celebrate with them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Because Your hand was on me, I sat alone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for You have filled me with indignation.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why is my pain unending,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my wound incurable,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "refusing to be healed?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have indeed become like a mirage to me—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "water that is not there.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The LORD’s Promise"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "Therefore this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“If you return, I will restore you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will stand in My presence.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And if you speak words that are noble instead of worthless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will be My spokesman.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It is they who must turn to you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but you must not turn to them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I will make you a wall to this people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a fortified wall of bronze;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will fight against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but will not overcome you,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for I am with you to save and deliver you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will deliver you from the hand of the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and redeem you from the grasp of the ruthless.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
